documentation.author: Knowledge & Discovery
documentation.explanation: Alert triggers any time an order with a route of IV is signed for a non-inpatient encounter. The rule checks for patient encounter class to ensure the patient is not an inpatient.
documentation.keywords: Modified on 4 13 2010 to include Intermittent IVs TW

templateDefinitions.name: EKS_ORDER_LIST_E
templateDefinitions.definition: an order ORD_METHOD OPT_ORDERS with status of OPT_ORDER_STATUS and an optional order detail of OPT_ORDER_DETAIL that OPT_QUALIFIER OPT_LIST

templateDefinitions.name: EKS_ORDER_LIST_INCOMING_L
templateDefinitions.definition: the triggering request contains an order ORD_METHOD OPT_ORDERS with status of OPT_ORDER_STATUS and an optional order detail of OPT_ORDER_DETAIL that OPT_QUALIFIER OPT_LIST

templateDefinitions.name: EKS_ORDERS_DETAIL_L

templateDefinitions.name: EKS_ENCOUNTER_DETAIL_L
templateDefinitions.definition: the patient's ENC_DETAIL QUAL DETAIL_VALUE for the same encounter as OPT_LINK

templateDefinitions.definition: Execute PROGRAM_NAME with parameters OPT_PARAM and link to OPT_LINK

templateDefinitions.name: EKS_SETUP_ADD_ORDERS_A
templateDefinitions.definition: Setup GROUP_NAME to add ORDERS with OPT_COMMENT_TYPE of OPT_COMMENT for OPT_SCOPE as OPT_LINK

templateDefinitions.name: EKS_SET_ORDER_DETAIL_DT_A
templateDefinitions.definition: SET_ACTION ORDER_DETAIL equal to OPT_ANCHOR_DT or inherit it from OPT_LINK, offset OPT_OFFSET_DAY days, OPT_OFFSET_HOUR hours and OPT_OFFSET_MIN minutes for orders setup in group(s) GROUP_NAME
